WEBVTT

NOTE
Lithium-Ion Battery Fire Simulation — AF31 Suppression Demonstration
Duration: ~1 minute 53 seconds

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:15.000
[Technical illustration showing the internal composition of a lithium-ion battery cell, as used in electric vehicles]

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:30.000
[Firefighter places battery tray on testing surface and prepares to apply blowtorch]

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:50.000
[Blowtorch applied to battery tray — batteries begin to heat and combust]

00:00:50.000 --> 00:01:05.000
[On-screen text: "Burning Lithium Battery" — intense flames visible from the battery tray]

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:25.000
[Firefighter applies AF31 water-based solution via portable extinguisher directly onto burning batteries]

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:40.000
[Flames extinguished completely — no re-ignition after AF31 application]

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:53.000
[On-screen text: "Eco-Friendly · Water Based · Unlimited Utility" — emphasizing AF31 effectiveness on all fire types]
